emale":"1170年–殁","about 1170":"大约1170年","1259":"1259年","1215":"1215年","1224":"1224年","1296":"1296年","1196":"1196年","1160":"1160年","about 1196":"大约1196年","1170":"1170年","England":"英国","Booton, Norfolk, England":"英国諾福爾可布托","lifeSummary":"Mrs Robert Howard于大约1170年出生在英国。她和Robert Hereward至少有1个儿子。"},"hr":{"about 1170–":"oko 1170.–preminula","1160–Male":"1160–preminuo","1196–1296":"1196–1296","1170–Female":"1170–preminula","about 1170":"oko 1170.","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1296":"1296","1196":"1196","1160":"1160","about 1196":"oko 1196.","1170":"1170","England":"England","Booton, Norfolk, England":"Booton, Norfolk, England"},"cs":{"about 1170–":"okolo 1170–Zesnulá","1160–Male":"1160–Zesnulý","1196–1296":"1196–1296","1170–Female":"1170–Zesnulá","about 1170":"okolo 1170","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1296":"1296","1196":"1196","1160":"1160","about 1196":"okolo 1196","1170":"1170","England":"Anglie","Booton, Norfolk, England":"Booton, Norfolk, Anglie"},"da":{"about 1170–":"omkring 1170–Afdød","1160–Male":"1160–Afdød","1196–1296":"1196–1296","1170–Female":"1170–Afdød","about 1170":"omkring 1170","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1296":"1296","1196":"1196","1160":"1160","about 1196":"omkring 1196","1170":"1170","England":"England","Booton, Norfolk, England":"Booton, Norfolk, England"},"nl":{"about 1170–":"circa 1170–Overleden","1160–Male":"1160–Overleden","1196–1296":"1196–1296","1170–Female":"1170–Overleden","about 1170":"circa 1170","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1296":"1296","1196":"1196","1160":"1160","about 1196":"circa 1196","1170":"1170","England":"England","Booton, Norfolk, England":"Booton, Norfolk, England"},"en":{"about 1170–":"about 1170–Deceased","1160–Male":"1160–Deceased","1196–1296":"1196–1296","1170–Female":"1170–Deceased","about 1170":"about 1170","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1296":"1296","1196":"1196","1160":"1160","about 1196":"about 1196","1170":"1170","England":"England","Booton, Norfolk, England":"Booton, Norfolk, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Robert","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Andre, Marcel, Gilles, Normand, Armand, Lucien, Pierre, Emile, Michel, Edouard, Gaston, Yves.","French, Walloon, English, German, Dutch, Flemish, and Breton (of French origin); Hungarian (<b>Róbert</b>): from the ancient Germanic personal name <i>Ro(d)bert</i> (Middle English <i>Robert</i>, Old French <i>Ro(d)bert</i>), composed of the elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame, renown’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’. This is found occasionally in Anglo-Saxon England before the Conquest, but in the main it was introduced into England by the Normans and quickly became popular among all classes of society. Pet forms and diminutives are found from an early date,   Robin   being particularly common. Compare   Robair  ,   Robar  ,   Robare  , and   Rober  .","In some cases also an Americanized form of one or more similar (like-sounding) Jewish surnames."],"variants":[{"name":"Rabbitt","meanings":["English: from the Middle English male personal name <i>Rabbode</i>, <i>Radboda</i> (ancient Germanic <i>Radbodo</i>, from elements meaning ‘counsel’ + ‘messenger’).","English: from the personal name <i>Robet</i> or <i>Robot</i>, diminutives of <i>Rob</i> (see   Robert  ).","English: nickname from late Middle English <i>rabet</i> ‘young rabbit’. This word is not recorded until <i>c.</i> 1398, the usual Middle English word for ‘rabbit’ being <i>cony</i> (see   Coney  )."]},{"name":"McRobbie","meanings":["Scottish (Aberdeenshire): patronymic meaning ‘son of Robbie’, from the personal name <i>Robbie</i>, a Scottish pet form of   Robert  , with the Gaelic prefix <i>mac</i> ‘son of’."]},{"name":"Rabjohn","meanings":["English (Devon, Essex): from the Middle English personal name <i>Robechon</i> (of Norman French origin: Old Picard <i>Robichon</i>, Old French <i>Robeçun</i>), a double diminutive of <i>Rob</i>, a pet form of   Robert  , altered by folk etymology to <i>Robjohn</i> and <i>Rabjohn</i>."]},{"name":"Nabb","meanings":["English (Lancashire): topographic name for someone who lived by a <i>nab</i>, Middle English <i>nabbe</i> ‘hillock, knoll’ (Old Norse <i>nabbi</i> ‘projecting peak, hill’), or a habitational name from any of the many minor places in northern and eastern England named with this word, for example Whalley Nab in Blackburn (Lancashire), Nab Scar in Rydal (Westmorland), and The Nab in Burgh Saint Margaret (Norfolk).","English (Lancashire): alternatively, it may be from the Middle English personal names <i>Nabb</i> and <i>Napp</i>, which are probably parallels to <i>Nobb</i> and <i>Nopp</i>, pet forms of   Robert  . Compare   Nobbs  .","Scottish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac an Aba(dh)</b> ‘son of the abbot’, see   McNab  ."]},{"name":"Probert","meanings":["Welsh: Anglicized form of Welsh <i>ap Roppert</i> ‘son of Robert’(see   Robert  )."]},{"name":"Rabb","meanings":["Scottish and English (Lancashire): from the Middle English personal name <i>Rab(b)</i>, a pet form of   Robert   with unrounding of the first vowel. Compare   Robb  .","Hungarian: variant of   Rab  ."]},{"name":"Rapson","meanings":["English: patronymic from the Middle English personal name <i>Rab(b)</i> (a pet form of   Robert   with unrounding of the first vowel) + <i>-son</i>, with devoicing of /b/ to /p/. Compare   Robson   and   Rabb  ."]},{"name":"McCobb","meanings":["Irish: from <b>Mac Hob</b>, ‘son of <i>Hob</i> ‘, an English pet form of   Robert  . Compare   Hobson  ."]},{"name":"McRoberts","meanings":["Scottish and northern Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Roibeirt</b>, a patronymic from a Gaelic form of the personal name   Robert  , with English excrescent <i>-s</i>."]},{"name":"Robin","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Pierre, Andre, Emile, Marcel, Achille, Armand, Arnaud, Camille, Julien, Michel, Normand.","French, Breton, Scottish, English, and German: from the personal name <i>Robin</i>, a pet form of   Robert  , composed of the short form <i>Rob</i> + the hypocoristic suffix <i>-in</i>.","Slovenian: topographic name derived from <i>rob</i> ‘edge, border’ (see   Robar  )."]}]},{"name":"Howard","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Transferred use of the surname of an English noble family. The surname has a large number of possible origins, but in the case of the noble family early forms often have the spelling <i>Haward</i>, and so it is probably from a Scandinavian personal name derived from <i>hā</i> ‘high’ + <i>varðr</i> ‘guardian’. (The traditional derivation from the Old English name <i>Hereweard</i> ‘army guardian’ is untenable.) It is now a widespread given name."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":45,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705188,"age":54,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705189,"age":89,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs Robert Howard was born about 1170, in England. She had at least 1 son with Robert Hereward."},"et":{"about 1170–":"umbes 1170–Surnud","1160–Male":"1160–Surnud","1196–1296":"1196–1296","1170–Female":"1170–Surnud","about 1170":"umbes 1170","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1296":"1296","1196":"1196","1160":"1160","about 1196":"umbes 1196","1170":"1170","England":"England","Booton, Norfolk, England":"Booton, Norfolk, England"},"fi":{"about 1170–":"noin 1170–Kuollut","1160–Male":"1160–Kuollut","1196–1296":"1196–1296","1170–Female":"1170–Kuollut","about 1170":"noin 1170","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1296":"1296","1196":"1196","1160":"1160","about 1196":"noin 1196","1170":"1170","England":"England","Booton, Norfolk, England":"Booton, Norfolk, England"},"fr":{"about 1170–":"environ 1170–Décédée","1160–Male":"1160–Décédé","1196–1296":"1196–1296","1170–Female":"1170–Décédée","about 1170":"environ 1170","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1296":"1296","1196":"1196","1160":"1160","about 1196":"environ 1196","1170":"1170","England":"Angleterre","Booton, Norfolk, England":"Booton, Norfolk, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Mrs Robert Howard est née environ 1170, à Angleterre. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec Robert Hereward."},"de":{"about 1170–":"um 1170–Verstorben","1160–Male":"1160–Verstorben","1196–1296":"1196–1296","1170–Female":"1170–Verstorben","about 1170":"um 1170","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1296":"1296","1196":"1196","1160":"1160","about 1196":"um 1196","1170":"1170","England":"England","Booton, Norfolk, England":"Booton, Norfolk, England","lifeSummary":"Mrs Robert Howard wurde um 1170 in England geboren. Sie hatte mit Robert Hereward mindestens 1 Sohn."},"ht":{"about 1170–":"about 1170–Desede","1160–Male":"1160–Desede","1196–1296":"1196–1296","1170–Female":"1170–Desede","about 1170":"about 1170","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1296":"1296","1196"